result.execSummary:
The defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endangering Safety by Use of Dangerous Weapon (Under the Influence of Intoxicant), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.

COURT ORDERED Defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 0 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work and school.   REPORT DATE by  03-09-2016 by 05:00 p.m.  (1700 hours).

COURT ORDERED THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS:
*  Pay costs, surcharges, assessments, supervision, and DNA fees due on or before  05-24-2016.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab for testing.
*  Court does not object to Electronic Monitoring.

Received and filed with court:
*  Sentencing Referral Form
*  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief Form

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case scheduled for sentencing hearing.  Defense requests an adjourned sentencing date.  State takes no position.  Court grants request.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 24, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Court grants defense request to adjourn sentencing.   Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 45.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 19, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case scheduled for plea and sentencing.  Attorney Shellow unable to appear due to illness.  Case adjourned to Branch 34.  Bailiff provided next court date to defendant.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 11, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defense requests a Plea and Sentencing date. Court grants defense request. Case adjourned to branch 45.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 24, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Attorney Shellow unable to appear in court due to a personal emergency.  Clerk selected an adjourned date with Atty Shellow.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 45.  Status conference scheduled for October 28, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Status Conference, defense counsel requested an adjournment. Case adjourned to branch 45.   Parties are notified that effective September 14, 2015 this case will be reassigned to Judge Michelle Ackerman Havas, Branch 45 in Room 515 of the Courthouse.  Status conference scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense counsel requests matter be set for a status conference. Case adjourned to branch 23.  Status conference scheduled for September 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Absolute Sobriety.
Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription, no dangerous weapons or firearms.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Keyuia Sheneh Paige in court with attorney Robin Shellow.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge, Branch 45.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to Defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 45.
Parties advised that effective August 1, 2015, this case will be assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23, room 515.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 7/13/15 @ 1:30pm
